course_objective:
The main aim of this course is for students to obtain critical knowledge of the oldest known philosophical traditions, as well as insight into the coherence and importance of these traditions.
After successfully completing this course, students will be able to
describe in their own words, and using core philosophical notions, the development and schools of philosophy in the Greco-Roman traditions;
describe in their own words, and using core philosophical notions, the development and schools of philosophy in the Chinese and Sanskrit traditions;
describe interconnections between the above traditions;
analyse at a basic level primary sources from the above traditions.

Het voornaamste doel van deze cursus is studenten kritische kennis te laten verwerven van de oudste filosofische tradities, alsmede inzicht in de samenhang en het belang van die tradities.
Na succesvolle afronding van deze cursus, zal de student in staat zijn
in eigen woorden en met gebruik van centrale filosofische begrippen, de ontwikkeling en scholen van de filosofie in de Grieks-Latijnse tradities te beschrijven;
in eigen woorden en met gebruik van centrale filosofische begrippen, de ontwikkeling en scholen van de filosofie in de Chinese en Sanskriet-tradities te beschrijven;
dwarsverbanden tussen de genoemde filosofische tradities de beschrijven;
(vertaalde) primaire bronnen uit de genoemde filosofische tradities te analyseren op een basaal niveau.

De student:
verwerft kennis van en inzicht in basisconcepten en -theorieën uit de epistemologie;
leert die concepten en theorieën toepassen om vragen over kennis te analyseren en beantwoorden;
krijgt oog voor kennistheoretische vragen en problemen in maatschappelijke discussies;
leert de basisbeginselen van wetenschappelijk-filosofisch lezen, denken, analyseren, schrijven en discussiëren.

This course provides an overview of the development of economic thought as well as an insight into the relevance of economic theories for important current economic issues.
After successfully completing this course, you can:
Academic Skills:
explain the economic way of thinking;
identify fundamental questions in economics;
place economics as a discipline in relation to other social sciences.
Bridging Theory and Practice - Knowledge:
describe the most important economic concepts;
explain the role of different institutions in the economic process;
identify the main differences and similarities between various economic schools;
appoint the different fields of study of the program.
Bridging Theory and Practice - Application:
understand various forms of market and government failure;
analyze current policy proposals from an economic perspective.
Broadening Your Horizon:
name the most important works of prominent thinkers in economic science;
situate economic theories in a social, political and historical context.
Self Awareness:
define their own position and attitude with regards to different economic schools of thought;
constructively engage with positions and attitudes that differ from their own.

